## 🧾 1.9 Summary (Conceptual Recap)

A web application represents a **modern evolution** of software delivery — centralizing logic, simplifying access, and enabling global reach.\
Its power lies in its architecture: a **client-server model** that separates concerns between presentation, logic, and data layers.

From the early static pages of the 1990s to today’s intelligent, responsive, and AI-driven applications, the web has transformed into a living ecosystem where applications are accessible, interactive, and continually evolving.
